1
00:00:06.500 --> 00:00:11.620
Ladybug is still here. I can feel it. She must have transformed back. She's vulnerable.

2
00:00:11.620 --> 00:00:15.000
Make sure that the others keep looking for Cat Noir. I'm going to give a personal, proper

3
00:00:15.000 --> 00:00:19.360
welcome to Ladybug. Stomp. Your power is now mine.

4
00:00:19.360 --> 00:00:23.720
Gabriel-san, don't put yourself at risk for nothing. Just let the plan unfold and we'll...

5
00:00:23.720 --> 00:00:28.200
Draw. Let me be, Tsurugi-san. I know what I'm doing. Fortunately, I won't be needing

6
00:00:28.200 --> 00:00:32.680
you much longer. Kagami...

7
00:00:32.680 --> 00:00:38.640
Yes? Gabriel has cut me off the system. His obsession

8
00:00:38.640 --> 00:00:48.960
may cause us to lose everything. Go to his mansion. Be my eyes and arms.

9
00:00:48.960 --> 00:00:55.960
In the daytime, I'm Marinette. Just a normal girl with a normal life. But there's something

10
00:00:55.960 --> 00:00:59.960
about that. No one knows it. Because I've got a secret.

11
00:00:59.960 --> 00:01:05.960
Miraculous. Simply the best. After the death, when things go wrong.

12
00:01:05.960 --> 00:01:11.960
Miraculous. The luckiest. The power of devil weighs so strong.

13
00:01:11.960 --> 00:01:15.960
Miraculous. Miraculous.

14
00:01:15.960 --> 00:01:23.960
Have a nice day, sir. Wait. Hello. Sorry, these ones are special. They're

15
00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:28.960
for Adrien. What surprise have you come up with this

16
00:01:28.960 --> 00:01:32.960
time, Marinette? I'll tell you, but only after I'm sure it's

17
00:01:32.960 --> 00:02:01.960
a birdhouse. A bag of seeds. And a bird whistle.

18
00:02:03.960 --> 00:02:05.960
I've got it!

19
00:02:05.960 --> 00:02:21.960
Hello, pretty dove.

20
00:02:21.960 --> 00:02:29.960
Have a good day. I love you, Marinette.

21
00:02:31.960 --> 00:02:34.960
Thanks for the surprise, Marinette. I love you, too.

22
00:02:34.960 --> 00:02:37.960
Thanks for the surprise, Marinette. I love you, too.

23
00:02:37.960 --> 00:02:43.960
You really are the superhero of surprises. Marinette is so wonderful. She always does

24
00:02:43.960 --> 00:02:47.960
amazingly creative things for me, like the surprise. Well, the only thing I can do is

25
00:02:47.960 --> 00:02:51.960
send her a voice message. No one expects a cheese maker to be great

26
00:02:51.960 --> 00:02:56.960
at sewing, too. Yet everyone knows that cheese makers are exceptional beings.

27
00:02:56.960 --> 00:02:59.960
Of course. You're right, Plagg. I know.

28
00:02:59.960 --> 00:03:02.960
So, what do you think? When we talked about finding a hiding place,

29
00:03:02.960 --> 00:03:04.960
I thought of a lot of spots, but never this.

30
00:03:04.960 --> 00:03:09.960
Believe me, it's the safest option. I love you, too.

31
00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:21.960
If I had mentioned mechanics, would you have built her a moped?

32
00:03:21.960 --> 00:03:24.960
No, Plagg. I chose knitting because Marinette is passionate about fashion

33
00:03:24.960 --> 00:03:27.960
design, and I'm sure she won't be expecting this surprise.

34
00:03:29.960 --> 00:03:32.960
Oh, it's a towel. A hand towel?

35
00:03:32.960 --> 00:03:35.960
Uh, no, Marinette. Actually, it's a t-shirt.

36
00:03:35.960 --> 00:03:39.960
Oh, right. Of course it's a t-shirt. These bigger holes are for arms.

37
00:03:39.960 --> 00:03:43.960
This is so surprising, Adrian. That's so nice of you. Thank you.

38
00:03:43.960 --> 00:03:47.960
Mother, I'm going out.

39
00:03:47.960 --> 00:03:49.960
What about your ikebana class?

40
00:03:49.960 --> 00:03:53.960
We've discussed this. I'm no longer wasting time making boring flower arrangements.

41
00:03:53.960 --> 00:03:55.960
You'd rather waste your time with that boy?

42
00:03:55.960 --> 00:03:58.960
Felix isn't just a boy.

43
00:03:58.960 --> 00:04:00.960
They love each other, and love won't wait.

44
00:04:00.960 --> 00:04:03.960
After all I've done for you, after everything I've lost,

45
00:04:03.960 --> 00:04:05.960
how can you put your life in the hands of a monster

46
00:04:05.960 --> 00:04:07.960
who could be rid of you with the snap of his fingers?

47
00:04:07.960 --> 00:04:10.960
Felix would never do that. He's helping me find meaning to my life

48
00:04:10.960 --> 00:04:12.960
instead of trying to control it like you always did.

49
00:04:12.960 --> 00:04:15.960
The only monster here isn't Felix or me. It's you.

50
00:04:15.960 --> 00:04:18.960
Insolent girl. Whether you like it or not, you are a tsurugi.

51
00:04:18.960 --> 00:04:20.960
You are not worthy of wearing our family ring.

52
00:04:20.960 --> 00:04:22.960
You'll earn it back again when you respect our values.

53
00:04:22.960 --> 00:04:24.960
Long, break the storm!

54
00:04:29.960 --> 00:04:30.960
Oh!

55
00:04:30.960 --> 00:04:33.960
You're the one who hasn't kept her promise, Mother.

56
00:04:33.960 --> 00:04:35.960
I allowed you to go to school.

57
00:04:35.960 --> 00:04:37.960
And I saved you from humiliation!

58
00:04:37.960 --> 00:04:39.960
You and Monarch's accomplice, remember?

59
00:04:39.960 --> 00:04:42.960
If it weren't for me, Ladybug would have brought you to justice.

60
00:04:42.960 --> 00:04:45.960
But I promised her that you'd change, that she trusted me.

61
00:04:45.960 --> 00:04:48.960
Enough to hide what you and Gabriel Agrest did from the whole world!

62
00:04:48.960 --> 00:04:52.960
Enough to leave me the dragon miraculous knowing I live in the same room as you!

63
00:04:52.960 --> 00:04:57.960
I should stop loving you for everything you've done.

64
00:04:57.960 --> 00:05:01.960
But I can't. Adrian has lost his father forever.

65
00:05:01.960 --> 00:05:06.960
Do you realize how lucky we are to still have each other?

66
00:05:06.960 --> 00:05:08.960
Please don't ruin everything.

67
00:05:08.960 --> 00:05:10.960
Wind Dragon.

68
00:05:10.960 --> 00:05:17.960
I'm not as creative as Marinette.

69
00:05:17.960 --> 00:05:19.960
But this cake is bound to help me measure up.

70
00:05:19.960 --> 00:05:24.960
Do you really want to give a cake to a baker's daughter?

71
00:05:25.960 --> 00:05:29.960
You're right. Why would she want a cake from me when she can have all she wants at home?

72
00:05:29.960 --> 00:05:30.960
The best in Paris.

73
00:05:30.960 --> 00:05:33.960
But then what could make her happy?

74
00:05:33.960 --> 00:05:35.960
I have an idea.

75
00:05:35.960 --> 00:05:38.960
What is he doing with that large hunk of meat?

76
00:05:38.960 --> 00:05:42.960
Are you really sure about this?

77
00:05:42.960 --> 00:05:48.960
Absolutely. Beef rib is a no-brainer when it comes to romance a la Francais.

78
00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:51.960
Hey!

79
00:05:53.960 --> 00:05:55.960
I think I'm gonna need another idea.

80
00:05:55.960 --> 00:05:57.960
Or just another beef rib.

81
00:06:23.960 --> 00:06:35.960
[phone rings]

82
00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:37.960
Tsurugi-san.

83
00:06:37.960 --> 00:06:41.960
Gabriel-san. I knew you'd call for my help eventually.

84
00:06:41.960 --> 00:06:44.960
Lady Bug and Cat Noir are stronger than I anticipated.

85
00:06:44.960 --> 00:06:46.960
Or rather, you are too weak.

86
00:06:46.960 --> 00:06:48.960
There are two of them, and I'm just one.

87
00:06:48.960 --> 00:06:51.960
But with your help, I could repair the Peacock Miraculous. Then Natalie could join me.

88
00:06:51.960 --> 00:06:54.960
That's out of the question. I'm never touching that wretched Miraculous again.

89
00:06:54.960 --> 00:06:57.960
The price I paid to have Kagami using his magic was high enough.

90
00:06:57.960 --> 00:07:01.960
As for you, I thought losing your wife would have brought you to your senses.

91
00:07:01.960 --> 00:07:05.960
Playing supervillains. You're disgracing yourself, Gabriel.

92
00:07:05.960 --> 00:07:10.960
Tamui, if you help me attain Lady Bug and Cat Noir's Miraculous, we'll make the wish together.

93
00:07:10.960 --> 00:07:13.960
I'll get my wife back, and you'll get your eyes back.

94
00:07:13.960 --> 00:07:15.960
That would mean betraying the kingdom.

95
00:07:15.960 --> 00:07:18.960
Are you having qualms? I wasn't aware of such weakness in you.

96
00:07:18.960 --> 00:07:20.960
How can I be sure you won't betray me as well?

97
00:07:20.960 --> 00:07:23.960
What proof of my loyalty do you need?

98
00:07:23.960 --> 00:07:29.960
I have been disappointed by men my entire life.

99
00:07:29.960 --> 00:07:35.960
I want Kagami to grow up to have a prince charming as perfect as she is.

100
00:07:35.960 --> 00:07:40.960
Smart, strong, handsome, and obedient.

101
00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:42.960
Someone like my son.

102
00:07:42.960 --> 00:07:44.960
Perhaps. Let's introduce them first.

103
00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:49.960
If your lineage proves worthy of uniting with mine, I might consider helping you.

104
00:07:50.960 --> 00:07:55.960
[Footsteps]

105
00:07:55.960 --> 00:08:06.960
Perfect.

106
00:08:06.960 --> 00:08:07.960
Kagami.

107
00:08:07.960 --> 00:08:09.960
Yes, Mother?

108
00:08:09.960 --> 00:08:11.960
How would you like to move to Paris?

109
00:08:11.960 --> 00:08:15.960
Hello, Mother.

110
00:08:15.960 --> 00:08:19.960
Forgive my intrusion, but I've sensed your disappointment, so I thought I'd pay you a little visit.

111
00:08:19.960 --> 00:08:21.960
Nuru, dark wings rise.

112
00:08:21.960 --> 00:08:24.960
Kagami was so perfect.

113
00:08:24.960 --> 00:08:28.960
It must be so painful to feel your favorite daughter escape from your grasp.

114
00:08:28.960 --> 00:08:31.960
Luckily, I am here.

115
00:08:31.960 --> 00:08:33.960
What do you want, Laila?

116
00:08:33.960 --> 00:08:35.960
To help you.

117
00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:38.960
It must be hard playing the kind mother.

118
00:08:38.960 --> 00:08:42.960
You know as well as I do that I have no choice if I want my freedom.

119
00:08:42.960 --> 00:08:45.960
Things would be so much easier if Kagami obeyed you again, wouldn't they?

120
00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:48.960
As long as Kagami bears the ring holding the muck that I used to give birth to her,

121
00:08:48.960 --> 00:08:51.960
I cannot control her.

122
00:08:51.960 --> 00:08:53.960
She will do whatever she wants.

123
00:08:53.960 --> 00:08:58.960
You might not be able to control her, but you could control the company she keeps.

124
00:08:58.960 --> 00:09:01.960
Would you like to hear about the plan I've devised?

125
00:09:01.960 --> 00:09:04.960
First, I'll akumatize you.

126
00:09:04.960 --> 00:09:08.960
Once you've become a supervillain, you'll capture Felix.

127
00:09:08.960 --> 00:09:12.960
I'll be waiting for Felix inside your armor.

128
00:09:12.960 --> 00:09:15.960
Since Felix too, like Kagami, is connected to the magic of an amok,

129
00:09:15.960 --> 00:09:21.960
the only thing left for me to do will be to seize the object of control, his signet ring.

130
00:09:21.960 --> 00:09:25.960
From now on, you will be a spy within the Miraculars.

131
00:09:25.960 --> 00:09:30.960
You'll give us all the information we need to seize Ladybug and Cat Noir's Miraculous.

132
00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:31.960
At your command.

133
00:09:31.960 --> 00:09:36.960
Once I've replaced his ring with a forgery, you'll drop me off in a quiet place.

134
00:09:36.960 --> 00:09:39.960
Then you'll pretend you've seen the error of your ways,

135
00:09:39.960 --> 00:09:42.960
and in a final effort you'll reject the Ultrakuma,

136
00:09:42.960 --> 00:09:45.960
unapologized to Kagami, telling her...

137
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:47.960
I've realized my errors, Kagami.

138
00:09:47.960 --> 00:09:51.960
And from now on, I'll let you live your life with Felix.

139
00:09:51.960 --> 00:09:54.960
Kagami will be happy to be reunited with her boyfriend,

140
00:09:54.960 --> 00:09:59.960
except he will no longer be her Felix, but our Felix.

141
00:09:59.960 --> 00:10:04.960
You can no longer control your daughter, but you'll be able to control her boyfriend.

142
00:10:04.960 --> 00:10:07.960
How do I know you'll stick to your word this time?

143
00:10:07.960 --> 00:10:10.960
I'm only doing what's in your best interest.

144
00:10:10.960 --> 00:10:22.960
It's my mother again.

145
00:10:22.960 --> 00:10:24.960
Something wrong?

146
00:10:24.960 --> 00:10:27.960
Everything's fine now that you're here.

147
00:10:27.960 --> 00:10:29.960
Are you sure Marinette will agree?

148
00:10:29.960 --> 00:10:32.960
Can you imagine Marinette refusing to help someone?

149
00:10:32.960 --> 00:10:34.960
Of course you're right.

150
00:10:34.960 --> 00:10:40.960
What a strange optic, Marinette. What is it for?

151
00:10:40.960 --> 00:10:44.960
It's a special hanger for Adrien's special T-shirt.

152
00:10:44.960 --> 00:10:46.960
This T-shirt would be perfect for someone with four arms.

153
00:10:46.960 --> 00:10:48.960
It's the thought that counts, Tiki.

154
00:10:48.960 --> 00:10:52.960
Ryuko? Argos?

155
00:10:52.960 --> 00:10:54.960
Why do they want to see you?

156
00:10:54.960 --> 00:10:56.960
We're about to find out.

157
00:10:56.960 --> 00:10:58.960
We need you, Marinette.

158
00:10:58.960 --> 00:10:59.960
What's going on?

159
00:10:59.960 --> 00:11:02.960
You know our secret. You know that our mothers carried us like any children,

160
00:11:02.960 --> 00:11:04.960
but since they used the Peacock Miraculous,

161
00:11:04.960 --> 00:11:08.960
our existences are bound by its magic, which makes us especially vulnerable.

162
00:11:08.960 --> 00:11:11.960
Whoever has the Peacock Miraculous has the power of life and death

163
00:11:11.960 --> 00:11:13.960
over every being created by its magic.

164
00:11:13.960 --> 00:11:16.960
Now that I'm the holder, we know for sure no one will use it for evil.

165
00:11:16.960 --> 00:11:18.960
No one can destroy us with the snap of their fingers.

166
00:11:18.960 --> 00:11:20.960
But then what's the problem?

167
00:11:20.960 --> 00:11:22.960
Storm subsides.

168
00:11:22.960 --> 00:11:26.960
The problem, Marinette, is our rings.

169
00:11:26.960 --> 00:11:30.960
The amok holding the magic of the Peacock Miraculous was deposited into them.

170
00:11:30.960 --> 00:11:33.960
If someone were to seize them, we'd have no choice but to obey them.

171
00:11:33.960 --> 00:11:35.960
If they got damaged, we'd become seriously ill.

172
00:11:35.960 --> 00:11:37.960
And if they got destroyed, we'd disappear.

173
00:11:37.960 --> 00:11:39.960
Living with this knowledge is...

174
00:11:39.960 --> 00:11:42.960
I get it. You need me to put them somewhere safe, right?

175
00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:44.960
Yes, Marinette, that's right.

176
00:11:44.960 --> 00:11:47.960
We've considered everything.

177
00:11:47.960 --> 00:11:49.960
Burying them in an isolated place...

178
00:11:49.960 --> 00:11:51.960
But it's risky in case of future excavations or construction.

179
00:11:51.960 --> 00:11:53.960
Locking them in a safe, the bank...

180
00:11:53.960 --> 00:11:54.960
They could be stolen.

181
00:11:54.960 --> 00:11:56.960
Even sending them into space wouldn't be a solution.

182
00:11:56.960 --> 00:11:58.960
Cosmic radiation could damage them.

183
00:11:58.960 --> 00:12:02.960
And since we're also superheroes, we're running the risk of enemies badly enough for them.

184
00:12:02.960 --> 00:12:05.960
But you're here to see me because you already came up with a solution, haven't you?

185
00:12:05.960 --> 00:12:06.960
Yes. Magic.

186
00:12:06.960 --> 00:12:08.960
You're Yo-Yo's magic.

187
00:12:08.960 --> 00:12:10.960
This is very clever! Good job!

188
00:12:10.960 --> 00:12:11.960
Indeed.

189
00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:14.460
Once immersed in the field of possibilities of Ladybug's Yo-Yo,

190
00:12:14.460 --> 00:12:16.960
the rings could return to a Quantic state.

191
00:12:16.960 --> 00:12:20.960
Of course! And the only person in the universe who could access them would be...

192
00:12:20.960 --> 00:12:21.960
Ladybug!

193
00:12:21.960 --> 00:12:24.960
Hold on, hold on! Explain it to me again like I'm five years old!

194
00:12:24.960 --> 00:12:28.960
It means the rings would be stored in the form of magic puree in your Yo-Yo.

195
00:12:28.960 --> 00:12:31.960
And there'd be no risk of turning Kagami and Felix into puree too, right?

196
00:12:31.960 --> 00:12:34.460
There'd be absolutely no risk for them since the rings would still exist,

197
00:12:34.460 --> 00:12:36.960
but in the form of probabilities.

198
00:12:36.960 --> 00:12:39.960
Okay...

199
00:12:39.960 --> 00:12:42.960
And when you're not Ladybug, it'd be completely inaccessible.

200
00:12:42.960 --> 00:12:44.960
No Ladybug, no Yo-Yo, no Yo-Yo, no stealing the rings!

201
00:12:44.960 --> 00:12:46.960
It's a good idea, isn't it?

202
00:12:46.960 --> 00:12:49.293
I don't know.

203
00:12:49.293 --> 00:12:51.627
For a while I kept all the miraculous with me and my Yo-Yo,

204
00:12:51.627 --> 00:12:53.960
but that didn't stop Shadow Moth from stealing them from me.

205
00:12:53.960 --> 00:12:55.960
That wasn't your fault.

206
00:12:55.960 --> 00:12:58.960
There will always be a risk.

207
00:12:58.960 --> 00:13:02.960
But if there's one person who always finds a solution, it's you, Ladybug.

208
00:13:02.960 --> 00:13:09.960
Tiki, spots on!

209
00:13:14.960 --> 00:13:18.960
I'm touched by your trust, even though this is a great responsibility.

210
00:13:18.960 --> 00:13:24.960
You're entrusting me with your lives.

211
00:13:24.960 --> 00:13:27.960
You can decline. We don't want to force your hand.

212
00:13:27.960 --> 00:13:31.960
No, it's okay. I want to help you.

213
00:13:31.960 --> 00:13:33.960
Marinette!

214
00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:35.960
There's a surprise guest for you!

215
00:13:35.960 --> 00:13:37.960
Kagami, Felix, what are you doing here?

216
00:13:37.960 --> 00:13:39.960
We didn't even see you come in!

217
00:13:39.960 --> 00:13:40.960
Where's Marinette?

218
00:13:40.960 --> 00:13:42.960
I'm right here!

219
00:13:42.960 --> 00:13:46.960
Ah, great. I hope you're ready because I have another surprise for you.

220
00:13:46.960 --> 00:13:48.960
Uh, now?

221
00:13:48.960 --> 00:13:50.960
Ta-da! A beef rib!

222
00:13:50.960 --> 00:13:52.960
That's not a beef rib. Those are lamb chops.

223
00:13:52.960 --> 00:13:55.960
I know, but the butcher was out of beef ribs.

224
00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:57.960
Okay...

225
00:13:57.960 --> 00:14:00.960
With some garlic and rosemary, these will be delicious!

226
00:14:00.960 --> 00:14:03.960
I still can't figure out why you're here.

227
00:14:03.960 --> 00:14:06.960
The rings!

228
00:14:06.960 --> 00:14:07.960
What rings?

229
00:14:07.960 --> 00:14:08.960
You tell him!

230
00:14:08.960 --> 00:14:13.960
You know, we have these old family rings, and Kagami and I thought these old rings...

231
00:14:13.960 --> 00:14:19.960
You thought that... that we'd ask Marinette to help us hide them.

232
00:14:19.960 --> 00:14:21.960
Hide them? But why would you want to hide them?

233
00:14:21.960 --> 00:14:23.960
We want to hide them because it's romantic.

234
00:14:23.960 --> 00:14:24.960
Romantic?

235
00:14:24.960 --> 00:14:25.960
Yes. I read it in a manga.

236
00:14:25.960 --> 00:14:28.460
Wanting to give a gift to their future unborn children,

237
00:14:28.460 --> 00:14:30.960
the two sweethearts had cherished objects of theirs together.

238
00:14:30.960 --> 00:14:32.960
Oh, and where did they hide them?

239
00:14:32.960 --> 00:14:35.960
In a... tomb, right?

240
00:14:35.960 --> 00:14:37.960
And that's romantic?

241
00:14:37.960 --> 00:14:41.960
No, not at all. A purÃ©e is a terrible hiding place, and that's why Kagami and Felix came to see me.

242
00:14:41.960 --> 00:14:44.960
To come up with a better purÃ©e. I mean, a better idea than the one in the manga.

243
00:14:44.960 --> 00:14:46.960
Ah, what's your idea then?

244
00:14:46.960 --> 00:14:49.960
I'll tell you, but first you've got to help us find the rings,

245
00:14:49.960 --> 00:14:52.960
because no rings means no hiding place, and no hiding place means no idea.

246
00:14:52.960 --> 00:14:57.960
Ah! They were right there, look!

247
00:14:57.960 --> 00:14:58.960
The rings!

248
00:14:58.960 --> 00:15:01.460
Watch this, Marinette.

249
00:15:01.460 --> 00:15:03.960
I might not be the best when it comes to knitting or choosing meat, but I can do this.

250
00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:06.960
Magic.

251
00:15:06.960 --> 00:15:07.960
What have you done?

252
00:15:07.960 --> 00:15:08.960
Where are the rings?

253
00:15:08.960 --> 00:15:10.960
I watched a magic tutorial online.

254
00:15:10.960 --> 00:15:13.960
Not bad, huh?

255
00:15:13.960 --> 00:15:14.960
What about my ring?

256
00:15:14.960 --> 00:15:16.960
Felix, open your hand.

257
00:15:16.960 --> 00:15:19.960
Ta-da!

258
00:15:19.960 --> 00:15:23.960
You're being reckless, Adrian. You don't mess with valuables. Give me my ring back!

259
00:15:23.960 --> 00:15:26.960
It's just a magic trick, Felix. No need to panic.

260
00:15:26.960 --> 00:15:30.960
You're right, everything's fine. Why am I worrying?

261
00:15:36.960 --> 00:15:38.960
It's your mother, Kagami.

262
00:15:38.960 --> 00:15:42.960
Mother, that's enough! I don't want to talk to you right now!

263
00:15:42.960 --> 00:15:45.960
That's fine, Kagami. I just needed to know where you were.

264
00:15:45.960 --> 00:15:54.960
Felix Fathom, you are our bad influence! You'll never be anywhere near my daughter again!

265
00:15:54.960 --> 00:15:57.960
Mother, no!

266
00:15:57.960 --> 00:15:59.960
Felix!

267
00:15:59.960 --> 00:16:02.960
And you'll never transform again, either!

268
00:16:02.960 --> 00:16:05.960
Felix!

270
00:16:08.960 --> 00:16:25.960
This isn't his object of control, it's Kagami's!

271
00:16:25.960 --> 00:16:31.960
Adrian Agrest has Felix's ring!

272
00:16:31.960 --> 00:16:35.960
Adrian Agrest, you too won't be going anywhere near Kagami ever again!

273
00:16:35.960 --> 00:16:39.960
No, no, Mr. Ruby, you're mistaken. Kagami is just a friend. I'm in love with Marinette.

274
00:16:39.960 --> 00:16:40.960
I'm not taking any risks.

275
00:16:40.960 --> 00:16:41.960
Believing in Agrest!

276
00:16:41.960 --> 00:16:50.960
Aren't you two staying for lunch?

277
00:16:50.960 --> 00:16:52.960
Sorry, we have a small emergency.

278
00:16:52.960 --> 00:16:56.960
Where are Kagami and Adrian?

279
00:16:56.960 --> 00:16:59.960
Sabine, I don't think there'll be enough cutlets for everyone.

280
00:16:59.960 --> 00:17:02.960
Don't move. You'll be safe here.

281
00:17:02.960 --> 00:17:03.960
What about you?

282
00:17:03.960 --> 00:17:05.960
I'm going to get my mother away from here.

283
00:17:05.960 --> 00:17:07.960
Wouldn't it be safer if I kept it?

284
00:17:07.960 --> 00:17:08.960
I'd rather you didn't.

285
00:17:08.960 --> 00:17:12.460
Wow, she treats her boyfriend's ring with so much care.

286
00:17:12.460 --> 00:17:15.960
Do you think that's what being romantic looks like?

287
00:17:15.960 --> 00:17:17.960
Plagg, claw them!

288
00:17:17.960 --> 00:17:20.960
Mother, I'm here!

289
00:17:20.960 --> 00:17:25.960
My daughter has Felix's ring now.

290
00:17:34.960 --> 00:17:36.960
Plagg, break the storm!

291
00:18:04.960 --> 00:18:05.960
Water Dragon!

292
00:18:05.960 --> 00:18:16.960
Kagami, get back here!

293
00:18:16.960 --> 00:18:21.960
Kagami and Felix's lives are in danger. Tiki, spots on!

294
00:18:21.960 --> 00:18:24.960
Lucky Charm!

295
00:18:24.960 --> 00:18:32.960
Come to your senses. Prove to your daughter that you've changed!

296
00:18:34.960 --> 00:18:35.960
Not while she's with that boy!

297
00:18:35.960 --> 00:18:37.960
I'm in love with Felix, Mother!

298
00:18:37.960 --> 00:18:41.960
He's not meant for you. He'll end up hurting you, like Adrian, like every other boy!

299
00:18:41.960 --> 00:18:44.960
That's your choice. You want to keep being a supervillain?

300
00:18:44.960 --> 00:18:47.960
When you get out of control, I must get you on track. That's a mother's job.

301
00:18:47.960 --> 00:18:49.960
I don't choose my path or select who's worthy of my love!

302
00:18:49.960 --> 00:18:50.960
I am your mother!

303
00:18:50.960 --> 00:18:52.960
Keep that up and soon I won't be your son!

304
00:18:52.960 --> 00:18:53.960
Not a good girl!

305
00:19:01.960 --> 00:19:03.960
Where's your Ultra Akuma if it's not in there?

306
00:19:03.960 --> 00:19:04.960
Our plan won't work.

307
00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:08.960
Yoksi goes in. Help me escape without being noticed by the superheroes.

308
00:19:08.960 --> 00:19:22.960
Son, you have no feeling at all for me, Mother?

309
00:19:22.960 --> 00:19:27.960
Now!

310
00:19:28.960 --> 00:19:31.960
No! Get out of my hand! You won't fool me again!

311
00:19:31.960 --> 00:19:33.960
I don't want your wretched power anymore!

312
00:19:33.960 --> 00:19:36.960
This is all because I've been akumatized! I'm sorry, Kagami!

313
00:19:36.960 --> 00:19:39.960
You're perfect. Larger than life.

314
00:19:39.960 --> 00:19:53.960
I wouldn't want to lose my one and only daughter for the world. Can you forgive me?

315
00:19:59.960 --> 00:20:01.960
Storm subsides.

316
00:20:01.960 --> 00:20:04.960
I forgive you, Mother.

317
00:20:04.960 --> 00:20:16.960
Miraculous Ladybug!

318
00:20:16.960 --> 00:20:25.960
Kagami?

319
00:20:28.960 --> 00:20:29.960
*sigh*

320
00:20:29.960 --> 00:20:46.960
It's so romantic!

321
00:20:46.960 --> 00:20:49.960
It is, Kitty Cat. And it's perfect this way.

322
00:20:49.960 --> 00:20:52.960
Bound it!

323
00:20:58.960 --> 00:21:00.960
How touching.

324
00:21:00.960 --> 00:21:05.960
Lamb cutlets are a great gift idea.

325
00:21:05.960 --> 00:21:08.960
Yes, very unexpected.

326
00:21:08.960 --> 00:21:11.960
I know it's not as romantic as bearing rings in puree.

327
00:21:11.960 --> 00:21:15.960
I feel like nothing will ever be enough to show Marinette how much I love her.

328
00:21:15.960 --> 00:21:17.960
Oh, that's just too sweet.

329
00:21:17.960 --> 00:21:22.960
When Marinette does it, it's sweet. But when I do it, it's just playing weird.

330
00:21:22.960 --> 00:21:26.960
No, what's weird is when you try to do things my way.

331
00:21:26.960 --> 00:21:30.960
I'm usually the one who does weird things. You're Adrien. You do rational things.

332
00:21:30.960 --> 00:21:34.960
And it's not true that you don't do anything special for Marinette, Adrien.

333
00:21:34.960 --> 00:21:38.960
If it weren't for your cutlets, we wouldn't be sitting at this table together tonight.

334
00:21:38.960 --> 00:21:40.960
You're already a part of the family, kid.

335
00:21:40.960 --> 00:21:53.960
See, Sugarcube? A good meal is always a success.

336
00:21:56.960 --> 00:21:58.960
<i>Connection.</i>

337
00:21:58.960 --> 00:22:03.960
<i>The machine has joined us. We may begin.</i>

338
00:22:03.960 --> 00:22:05.960
<i>Gabriel Agrest was an exceptional diamond.</i>

339
00:22:05.960 --> 00:22:10.960
<i>It is my pleasure to introduce you to the new king of luxury, the new diamond.</i>

340
00:22:10.960 --> 00:22:12.960
<i>The diamond is dead.</i>

341
00:22:12.960 --> 00:22:14.960
<i>Long live the diamond!</i>

342
00:22:14.960 --> 00:22:18.960
<i>The diamond is dead.</i>

343
00:22:18.960 --> 00:22:20.960
<i>Long live the diamond!</i>

344
00:22:20.960 --> 00:22:22.960
<i>The diamond is dead.</i>

345
